otal bilirubin elevation greater than 2 times ULN, aminotransferase elevations are greater than 8 times ULN, or aminotransferase elevations persist beyond 2 weeks.', 'Synergism', 'The use of bedaquiline with other potentially hepatotoxic agents should be avoided whenever possible (e.', 'Moderate', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/113059/', '[1] "Product Information. Sirturo (bedaquiline)." Janssen Pharmaceuticals, Titusville, NJ.[2] "Product Information. Sirturo (bedaquiline)." Janssen Pharmaceuticals, Titusville, NJ.[3] "Product Information. Hivid (zalcitabine)." Roche Laboratories, Nutley, NJ.', 'Capreomycin, Rifamycin, Bedaquiline, Streptomycin, Cycloserine, Pyridoxine, Pretomanid, Tamsulosin, Tinidazole, Ascorbic acid, Hydroflumethiazide, More', 'Pyrazinamide, Rifamycin, Sulfamethoxazole, Rifapentine, Streptomycin, Trimethoprim, Cycloserine, Rifabutin, Isoniazid, Ethambutol, Ethionamide, More', 1767369485);
